\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. T. cernuum} Brot.,{\i   Phyt. Lusit.} ed. 3, {\b 1}: 150 (1816). Like {\b 20} but leaflets truncate or emarginate; pedicels 2 mm, about as long as the calyx-tube and longer than the bracts, strongly deflexed in fruit; calyx shorter than the corolla with teeth subequal, scarcely as long as the tube; petals pink; standard deeply emarginate.{\i   Dry, grassy places. S.W. Europe.} Az Co Ga Hs Lu.
