\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 23. T. suffocatum} L., {\i  Mantissa Alt. }276 (1771). Glabrescent, caespitose annual; stems 1-3(-5) cm, procumbent. Internodes rarely reaching 5 mm. Leaflets 3-8 mm, obovate-cuneate, emarginate; petioles 10-60 mm; stipules ovate, acuminate. Heads 5-6 mm, sessile, numerous, usually confluent, rarely somewhat separated, then ovate. Calyx sparsely pubescent at first, glabrescent; teeth all as long as the tube, lanceolate or subulate, recurved; corolla 3-4 mm, white; standard a little shorter than the calyx. Legume 2-seeded.{\i   Dry places. S. & W. Europe, northwards to} c. 53° 30' {\i  N in England}. Al Az Bl Br Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Rm Sa Si Tu.
\par

