\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. VESICASTRUM Ser. Bracts free or united into a small involucre. Flowers subsessile. Calyx inflated in fruit, upper lip externally densely hairy (rarely glabrous), scarious and reticulately veined, its two teeth often setaceous.
